cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a framework for approximating the explicit MPC law for linear parameter-varying systems using supervised learning techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Control Systems (cs.SY) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which further supports the likelihood of it belonging to the Machine Learning category. The paper also discusses the optimization of the learned policies, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper's focus on vehicle dynamics control suggests that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the paper's use of supervised learning techniques and neural networks suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
